{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17504193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17504193"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:12:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:12:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2308"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2308","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2308"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.45,0.26,0.07,0.22,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2308"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65077"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2308","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2308"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2308"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50513"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"434"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"2734"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"686"},{"type":"contributions","id":"702"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1260"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7283"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14268"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14772"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15469"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16227"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42467"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43122"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65077","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65077"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a history of falling one week ago. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. The fall was attributed to visual changes from her early cataracts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits except for blood pressure of 164/110 mmHg. There is no postural drop in blood pressure. Her BMI is 23 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. Her gait is normal and cardiovascular examination is unremarkable. An ECG shows normal sinus rhythm.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management of her blood pressure?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ambulatory blood pressure monitoring","Commence perindopril","Commence amlodipine","Review blood pressure in one week","Provide weight loss advice"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with an incidental finding of elevated blood pressure during assessment of a fall. Before initiating antihypertensive therapy, it is essential to confirm the diagnosis of hypertension, particularly in elderly patients who are at risk of falls.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmbulatory blood pressure monitoring\u003C/strong\u003E is the gold standard for diagnosing hypertension. It helps distinguish between true hypertension and white coat hypertension (elevated readings only in clinical settings). This is particularly important in elderly patients where unnecessary antihypertensive therapy could increase fall risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerindopril\u003C/strong\u003E, an ACE inhibitor, would be an appropriate first-line agent for confirmed hypertension. However, starting treatment before confirming the diagnosis could expose the patient to unnecessary medication risks.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmlodipine\u003C/strong\u003E, a calcium channel blocker, is another suitable first-line agent for hypertension. However, like perindopril, it should not be initiated until the diagnosis is confirmed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReview blood pressure in one week\u003C/strong\u003E would provide another clinic reading but would not help distinguish between true hypertension and white coat effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvision of weight loss advice\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as the primary intervention in this case, particularly as the patient already has a healthy BMI. While lifestyle modifications are important in managing hypertension, the first step here is to confirm the diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECurrent guidelines recommend ambulatory or home blood pressure monitoring before diagnosing hypertension, as treatment decisions based on clinic readings alone may lead to overtreatment, particularly in elderly patients who are at higher risk of medication side effects.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ambulatory blood pressure monitoring is recommended to confirm the diagnosis of hypertension before initiating treatment.","White coat hypertension should be excluded in elderly patients before starting antihypertensive medications due to fall risk.","A single elevated blood pressure reading in clinic is insufficient to diagnose hypertension."],"references":["Muntner P, Einhorn PT, Cushman WC, et al. Blood Pressure Assessment in Adults in Clinical Practice and Clinic-Based Research: JACC Scientific Expert Panel. J Am Coll Cardiol 2019; 73:317. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30678763/","Dolan E, Stanton A, Thijs L, et al. Superiority of ambulatory over clinic blood pressure measurement in predicting mortality: the Dublin outcome study. Hypertension 2005; 46:156. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15939805/","Shimbo D, Abdalla M, Falzon L, et al. Studies comparing ambulatory blood pressure and home blood pressure on cardiovascular disease and mortality outcomes: a systematic review. J Am Soc Hypertens 2016; 10:224. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26822864/","Nuredini G, Saunders A, Rajkumar C, et al. Current status of white coat hypertension: where are we? Ther Adv Cardiovasc Dis 2020; 14: 1\u201310. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32580646/","Guideline for the diagnosis and management of hypertension in adults. In: Heart Foundation [online]. 2016:37. Available at: https://www.heartfoundation.org.au/getmedia/c83511ab-835a-4fcf-96f5-88d770582ddc/PRO-167_Hypertension-guideline-2016_WEB.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50513"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2308"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50513","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50513"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T13:46:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T13:47:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2308"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65077"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"g